import { AiFillMobile } from "react-icons/ai"; import React, { useState } from "react"; export default function Contact() { const [form, setForm] = useState({ name: "", mobile: "", message: "" }); const [submitted, setSubmitted] = useState(false); const handleChange = (e) => { setForm({ ...form, [e.target.name]: e.target.value }); }; const handleSubmit = async (e) => { e.preventDefault(); try { // Make an HTTP POST request to the backend const response = await fetch( "https://yogapeth.onrender.com/submit-form", { method: "POST", headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify(form), } ); if (response.ok) { console.log("Form data submitted successfully"); alert("Thanks For Reaching US"); setSubmitted(true); setForm({ name: "", mobile: "", message: "" }); } else { console.error("Error submitting form data to backend"); } } catch (error) { console.error("An error occurred:", error); } }; return (
